WEBVTT

00:00.067 --> 00:01.565
<i>Previously on "Shades of Blue"...</i>

00:01.600 --> 00:03.520
<i>Lower the weapon, Detective Santos.</i>

00:03.545 --> 00:04.778
It's you who's under arrest.

00:04.813 --> 00:08.749
<i>Wozniak's convinced that
Saperstein's the mole.</i>

00:08.783 --> 00:09.917
<i>She's an escort</i>

00:09.951 --> 00:11.418
- What's your name?
- Harlee.

00:11.452 --> 00:13.677
Robert, your badge.

00:13.678 --> 00:15.245
<i>Stahl's unstable.</i>

00:15.280 --> 00:16.245
<i>He's become obsessed with me,</i>

00:16.280 --> 00:17.247
<i>and none of us feel safe.</i>

00:17.282 --> 00:18.916
<i>Your secrets have poisoned you.</i>

00:18.950 --> 00:20.551
But soon I'm gonna heal you.

00:20.585 --> 00:22.653
This is between us and Quince.

00:22.687 --> 00:25.556
You weren't supposed to look
in this bag here, were you?

00:25.590 --> 00:27.591
It's one thing running drugs;
it's a whole other thing

00:27.626 --> 00:29.760
when you make a little kid do it!

00:29.794 --> 00:32.396
My future is here with you.

00:32.430 --> 00:34.601
'Cause I love you.
I'm not going anywhere.

00:35.266 --> 00:37.771
<i>If you thought I was gonna
let you go that easily...</i>

00:38.803 --> 00:40.437
What did you do to me?

00:40.462 --> 00:42.776
<i>Your clothes got a little
dirty when I moved you.</i>

00:43.441 --> 00:44.842
Damn it!

00:44.876 --> 00:46.410
Why would you do this to yourself?

00:46.444 --> 00:47.411
Help me.

00:52.283 --> 00:53.283
<i>Lieutenant!</i>

00:53.318 --> 00:54.585
Quince took my mom.

00:56.321 --> 00:57.588
Somebody!

01:01.459 --> 01:07.152
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

01:11.176 --> 01:12.670
The witness will state her name, rank,

01:12.704 --> 01:14.438
and precinct for the record.

01:22.013 --> 01:23.380
Harlee Grace Santos,

01:23.415 --> 01:26.450
detective first grade, Brooklyn,

01:26.484 --> 01:28.111
the six four.

01:28.145 --> 01:30.688
You're assigned to
Lieutenant Matt Wozniak's

01:30.722 --> 01:32.556
so-called anti-crime unit.

01:32.590 --> 01:34.992
My duty and my home
for the past ten years.

01:35.026 --> 01:36.860
Except for a recent leave of absence,

01:36.895 --> 01:39.463
after which you underwent
psychological evaluation,

01:39.497 --> 01:40.531
is that right?

01:42.169 --> 01:43.458
Yes.

01:43.459 --> 01:46.127
And do you concur with
the assessment that cleared you

01:46.162 --> 01:49.297
for duty so soon
after a traumatizing abduction?

01:50.666 --> 01:53.263
I was shaky at first, but...

01:53.803 --> 01:55.437
I'm recovered now.

01:55.471 --> 01:57.372
I think it's important
to establish for the record

01:57.406 --> 01:59.441
that the events to which
you're about to testify

01:59.475 --> 02:03.178
took place after you survived
the ordeal in the woods

02:03.212 --> 02:05.347
and with your abductor still at large.

02:05.381 --> 02:08.027
Are you asking if I'm a reliable witness?

02:08.633 --> 02:10.551
If... if I'm crazy?

02:10.586 --> 02:12.287
Some of your actions after the incident

02:12.321 --> 02:14.289
could be perceived that way:

02:14.323 --> 02:15.824
rash, impulsive.

02:15.858 --> 02:17.492
I'm not gonna pretend
that former Agent Stahl

02:17.527 --> 02:19.540
didn't have an effect on me...

02:21.330 --> 02:25.963
more than I even knew or was
willing to admit to myself,

02:27.503 --> 02:29.371
But not in the way
that you're suggesting.

02:29.405 --> 02:31.473
In what way then?

02:31.507 --> 02:33.637
In the path that I've chosen;

02:34.343 --> 02:36.478
the decisions I've made;

02:36.512 --> 02:38.754
in the cop that I'm trying to be.

02:38.789 --> 02:40.482
So much so that now you're willing to

02:40.516 --> 02:44.853
identify criminal corruption
within the NYPD?

02:44.887 --> 02:46.655
I am.

02:46.689 --> 02:48.657
And how would you
characterize the corruption?

02:49.570 --> 02:51.493
Obstruction,

02:51.527 --> 02:53.240
racketeering...

02:54.283 --> 02:55.282
and murder.

02:56.435 --> 02:58.667
Involving active duty police officers?

02:59.788 --> 03:01.169
Correct.

03:01.203 --> 03:02.337
Including yourself?

03:04.907 --> 03:06.708
In a manner of speaking.

03:06.742 --> 03:08.743
Well, that begs the question

03:08.778 --> 03:12.009
and really defines this whole hearing.

03:12.782 --> 03:14.616
Detective Santos,
do you consider yourself

03:14.650 --> 03:18.219
more of a police officer or a criminal?

03:18.254 --> 03:19.683
Honestly?

03:22.144 --> 03:23.858
Depends on the day.

03:26.796 --> 03:28.775
Order, please.

03:29.231 --> 03:31.600
Then pick a day, Detective.

03:34.572 --> 03:36.572
_

03:38.000 --> 03:44.074
